features: ONE HAND ADJUST: With our new single hand adjustable headrest, keeping up with your child's growth has never been easier.
BUILT TO GROW: The All-in-One car seat built to grow for extended use through 3 stages: Rear-facing 5-40 pounds, Forward-facing 22-65 pounds, and Belt-positioning booster 40-100 pounds.
SIDE IMPACT PROTECTION: The Grow and Go Sprint's side impact protection helps keep your child safe. Plus, the 3-position recline makes it easy to get a good fit in your car.
EASY IN, EASY OUT: Harness holders keep the harness in an open position so it's easy to get your child in and out of the seat. Clearly visible booster belt path allows for easier buckling.

FUSS-FREE CLEANING: Machine washable and dryer safe seat pad features snaps that make it simple to take off of the seat for easy cleaning. Armrests for added comfort, include 2 removable, dishwasher-safe cup holders.
body.description: Get the car seat thats built to grow! From your first ride together coming home from the hospital to soccer day car pools, the Crosstown DLX Car Seat will give your child a safe and more comfortable ride. Featuring the new single hand adjustable headrest, you can adjust the headrest and harness as your little one gets bigger with just one hand and in one quick motion, without re-threading the harness or re-installing the car seat. Harness holders keep the harness straps out of the way, making it easier to get your child in and out of the car seat. As your tiny baby grows into a big kid, messes are bound to happen, but weve made cleaning easy. The seat pad snaps off easily without removing the harness and is machine washable and dryer safe. Dual cup holders transport favorite drinks and snacks and are easily removable and dishwasher safe. When your child is ready to use the vehicle seat belts, remove the harness for belt-positioning booster mode, suitable from 40-100 lbs. Buckling up with the vehicle belt is easy with the visible belt path guiding the way. Built for child comfort, the Crosstown DLX includes two removable grow-with-baby pillows to give your new travel companion a snug fit. Dual armrests provide added comfort for older kids on long car rides. The Crosstown DLX provides more comfort for parents too, taking up less space when placed rear-facing, giving up to 7 inches more legroom for parents in the front seat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Car seat fits greats in my car. It’s compact enough that I can keep my front seats comfortably but only when the seat is in the middle back seat. It’s a comfortable feeing seat for sure, looks great, baby doesn’t cry when riding in it which was an issue in her baby bucket seat…it’s easy to adjust the height of harness and the tightness of straps! We don’t use the shoulder pads right now as I had to take them off to get a proper fit for my little one when we first started to use the seat and she’s still on the smaller side for them…rear facing I love the seat recline adjustments it has-it’s got more than 1 spot that can be used which I love so much more than seats that don’t have that. The seat was so easy to instal it took me less than 5 mins to have a perfect instal and I didn’t have to fight it to get it in tight at all which shocked me. Sometimes to adjust the harness tightness I do fight with it-but not usually…The seat fabric is really cute and has held up amazing so far. It isn’t stained at all even after we had a blow out poop diaper and throw up happen in the car…which impressed me not gunna lie…I did not enjoy removing the cover of seat to wash it however and it was painful to put back together but it was doable…The crotch strap has 3 diff spots to adjust it to baby which I like…the instructions for the smallest size is confusing I’m glad we didn’t need to set it up that small…baby is now 19 pounds and 22 inches long and fits in the seat super comfortably she’s a little chunky girl and the width leaves her with more space than she needs which is why we upgraded her before she was sitting unsupported to a convertible seat rear facing as her bucket seat was way to narrow for her!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love it and my baby loves it!
reviews.reviewText: After days and days of research and comparing reviews I came across this carseat and I'm so glad I did! Previous to this carseat I bought an infant seat and my baby was outgrowing it come to find out we could've been using this all along was an eye opener, not to mention it converts into a front facing and booster... no need to buy another seat! This seat will save you money and time. The first time I put my child in this seat she was HAPPY, it must be so comfortable for her. Just by feeling it I can tell it's very padded and not to closed in that they feel crammed in there. Yet they did not skimp out on the safety features! This thing is sturdy once straped it, no wobbling or scooting, stays right in place, the seat belt goes inbetween the plastic and fabric so that there's so way the belt can slip off which my last seat did and always made me nervous. This thing has hit EVERY buying feature I looked for! #1 safety #2 comfort #3 affordable ( and #4 my child LOVES it! ) It also came with a recall form which provides me comfort in knowing they will get in touch with me if it becomes unsafe. Thank you for providing us with an affordable and safe product!

Compré dos, uno para mi niña de 2 años y medio y otro para mi bebé de 3 meses, los colores son vibrantes, el material es muy suave, en resumen son bonitos dice mi niña grande que está muy cómoda su sillita, tengo un auto compacto y entraron muy bien los dos, uno a contramarcha y el otro viendo hacia adelante, la instalación es muy fácil, si bien el instructivo viene en inglés técnico, hay videos que son de gran ayuda al momento de instalar, el primer día de uso tuvimos un choque por alcance y la bebé ni se despertó venía dormida y su hermanita tampoco se dió cuenta, gracias a Dios y a los asientos están de lo mejor, no les pasó nada, me gustó mucho que el mismo asiento se adapto perfecto a cada una por lo que le durará mucho tiempo a bebé y a su hermanita le servirá como Booster en un futuro, definitivamente es un excelente producto y si tienen bebés lo recomiendo ampliamente porque será su autoasiento por mucho tiempo

reviews.reviewTitle: EL SEGURO SE ATORA Y ES MUUUUY CALIENTE EL MATERIAL
reviews.reviewText: No doy 5 por que el botón del seguro es difícil de abrir, y eso puede ser contraproducente si ocupas sacar rápido al bebé, (ESPERO NO SEA DEFECTO DE FABRICA Y SOLO SEA POR QUE ES NUEVO), NO ME GUSTO QUE NO VENIA ENVUELTO PARA PROTECCIÓN, lo demás en lo personal me parece que está cumpliendo con lo que esperaba, está muy bonito y el material se siente de buena calidad, la bebecita al parecer va muy cómoda, me encanta que puedes utilizarlo en todo su crecimiento. Se me complicó instalarlo,creo por mi falta de experiencia, pero trae el instructivo. Editado 27-08-23 LA TELA ES MUY CALIENTE Y PASA MUCHO CALOR.
